question.title: Build Google SDK example with Eclipse with release mode

node.contents: I try to build Google Drive SDK examples in Eclipse v22.01: (The example website is as follows:) https://developers.google.com/drive/quickstart-android

astNode.text: I try to build Google Drive SDK examples in Eclipse v22.01: (The example website is as follows:) https://developers.google.com/drive/quickstart-android

node.contents: When I used debug build,it builded fine and executed fine on my table device. However, when I tried to build it on release mode, I failed.

astNode.text: When I used debug build,it builded fine and executed fine on my table device. However, when I tried to build it on release mode, I failed.

node.contents: My process is as follows: 1. Go to "File"->"Export" 2. Create private keystore (This step succeeded.) 3. Build apk

astNode.text: My process is as follows: 1. Go to "File"->"Export" 2. Create private keystore (This step succeeded.) 3. Build apk

node.contents: I've checked the post Update your Proguard and downloaded and replaced jars in Proguard I also checked the postCheck the '"Android Private Libraries' and checked items on "Order and Export" tab. But Still failed.

astNode.text: I've checked the post Update your Proguard and downloaded and replaced jars in Proguard I also checked the postCheck the '"Android Private Libraries' and checked items on "Order and Export" tab. But Still failed.

node.contents:
1. Just Uncheck the 'Drive API' (See the picture for reference) (I am not sure if 'Android Dependencies' is needed or not. Maybe this could also be unchecked.)

  2. I also add '-dontwarn com.google.**' to 'proguard-android.txt' And then it worked.
